<p>If you think about it since tag 18 is considered 0 degrees field centric, when you start your robot code your gyro resets for its starting yaw to be 0 degrees.</p>
<p>So if you put another tag in front of the robot without rotating the gyro properly the Limelight will think it can see the tag from its zero yaw position.</p>
<p>Basically you just need to rotate your robot to the yaw that it should be at, then place the tag in front of it, and it should work.</p>
<p>Hopefully that helps</p>","post_number":8,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-25T14:08:49.702Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":7,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":0,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":13.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":496835,"topic_slug":"limelight-localization-help","display_username":"Alexander Carlisi","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":57591,"username":"thaMan","name":"Tharun","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e5b9ba/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":62389,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/limelight-localization-help/496835/8","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3567979,"name":"Tharun","username":"thaMan","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/t/e5b9ba/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-25T14:12:51.300Z","cooked":"<p>Ah ok that makes so much more sense now. Now that I think about it all the tags that we were testing always were always some horizontal distance away from the tag which assuming that the tag was right infront of the bot with no rotation that would probabely explain why its not rotating. I just wanted to ask a quick followup in that if we were to rotate the bots gyro to the right angle and then put the tag in front of it would we expect to see the right values?</p>","post_number":9,"post_type":1,"posts_count":11,"updated_at":"2025-03-25T14:12:5